    - m_Type: 0
      Title:
        m_Untranslated: 
      Text:
        m_Untranslated: 'Unlike in the previous per-object lighting probe system,
          individual probes can not be moved or deleted. This is a hard limitation
          of the system. In cases where we would need to move a set of probes, we
          could use virtual offset instead.


          <b>Virtual offset</b> allows
          us to move the capture position of light probes. It can be enabled globally
          in the <b>Lighting</b> > <b>Probe Volumes</b> panel, automatically adjusting
          the capture position of probes that are inside geometry. Or it can be applied
          manually as we did for this project, by using Probe Adustment Volumes in
          a specified location.


          The bright line seen in the image is
          caused by the overly bright probes below the floor. To fix it, we added
          a probe adjustment volume that would virtually lift the said probes up
          by ~0.6 meters during the baking process.


          To undo the fix and
          explore the issue further, follow these steps:


          1. Move the
          cube to  <b>X:41 Y:0 Z:3</b>


          2. Disable the <b>Probe Adustment
          Volume</b> under <b>Lighting</b> > <b>Adaptive Probe Volumes</b> in the
          <i>Hierarchy</i> window.


          3. Rebake the lighting by using the
          <b>Generate Lighting.</b>'
